<title>
Seat Heater Wire Inspection (If Equipped)
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Confirm that seat heater switch is OFF.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect connector of seat heater under seat cushion.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Measure resistance between terminals as shown below. If resistance is out of specification, replace faulty seat cushion heater and/or seatback heater.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Seat heater circuit resistance
</title>
<ptxt>
Seat cushion side [A] (between terminal “B” and “C”, between terminal “A” and “C”): 4.7 – 5.7 &#937; at 20 &#176;C (68 &#176;F)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Seatback side [B] (between terminal “F” and “D”: 10.7 – 13.1 &#937; at 20 &#176;C (68 &#176;F)
</ptxt>
</spec>
